<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!DOCTYPE rpl PUBLIC "-//ROCKLYTE//DTD RPL 1.0//EN">

<body face="Noto Sans" font-size="10pt" margins="24"/>

<editdef name="bench_edit" on-change="bench_change"/>
<editdef name="bench_min" min-width="80"/>

<page name="Index">
   <script persistent type="fluid" name="flProject" @doc="{kt:self-id()}">
<![NDATA[

function bench_change()
end

]]>
   </script>

   <h1>Edit Cell Benchmark</h1>

   <p>The table below uses editable cells of varying content density so benchmark runs exercise edit-cell layout,
   minimum-size enforcement, and nested content placement.</p>

   <p><table width="100%" stroke="rgb(150,150,150)" cell-padding="6" spacing="4">
      <row fill="rgb(245,245,245)">
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><b>Title</b></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><b>Content</b></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
         <cell edit="bench_min"><p>Short</p></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><p>This editable cell contains a moderate amount of paragraph text for standard
         wrapping.</p></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
         <cell edit="bench_min"><p>Empty target follows</p></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
         <cell edit="bench_min"><p>Nested paragraph block</p></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><p>First paragraph inside the edit cell.</p><p>Second paragraph inside the edit
         cell.</p></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
         <cell edit="bench_min"><p>Long token</p></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><p>editable_cell_probe_token_with_no_break_positions_to_stress_width_management</p></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><p>Trailing</p></cell>
         <cell edit="bench_edit"><p>The final editable cell closes the table with normal content so row height and edit
         area bookkeeping can be compared against previous runs.</p></cell>
      </row>
   </table></p>
</page>
